# Frontend Dashboard Layout

ROW 1: Movie Spotlight (70%) + Collection Snapshot

ROW 2: Your Movie DNA (genre donut, stats, genre explorer)

ROW 3: Trending Movies

ROW 4: Collection Insights

ROW 5: Recommended Movies

Navigation, search, and profile layout must not be changed.

---

# Active Decisions

Use PostgreSQL.

Use Spring Data JPA.

Use Spring Security OAuth2 Client.

Use Google OAuth.

Use GitHub OAuth.

Use Spring WebClient.

Use Docker Compose.

Use Lombok.

Use Swagger/OpenAPI.

Frontend uses Next.js App Router, TanStack Query, Axios, Tailwind CSS.

API base URL: `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL` (default `http://localhost:8080`).

---

# Caching Strategy

Movie and Person records are stored locally.

When data is older than 7 days:

* Refresh from TMDb
* Update database
* Return updated data

Minimize TMDb requests.

---

# User Strategy

Users authenticate using OAuth.

User records are persisted.

Favorites are user-specific.

Users may only access their own favorites.

No local username/password authentication.

OAuth providers:

* Google
* GitHub

